<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1436,151,536]" pageId="21" pageNumber="282">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,537,151,176]" pageId="21" pageNumber="282">Comparisons and Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mayer" authorityYear="1974" box="[547,769,152,176]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="282" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pectinifer">
<emphasis box="[547,769,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="282">Epigonus pectinifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Giglioli" baseAuthorityYear="1880" box="[949,1117,152,176]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="282" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="constanciae">
<emphasis box="[949,1117,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="282">E. constanciae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group by having a pungent opercular spine (Okamoto 2012). Besides 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mayer" authorityYear="1974" box="[634,774,188,212]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="282" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pectinifer">
<emphasis box="[634,774,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="282">E. pectinifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[792,898,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="20.[151,250,1802,1824]" captionTargetBox="[188,1346,1182,1787]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[188,1398,1171,1787]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 16. Epigonus pectinifer. A: SAIAB 86380, 1 of 3 specimens, 152.6 mm SL; B: dorsal view of snout of SAIAB 193895, 1 of 4 specimens, 80.0 mm SL (arrows show the maxillary mustache-like processes)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1182201/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="282">Fig. 16A</figureCitation>
), 6 species of this species group, including the two new species described in the present study, are distributed in the 
<collectingRegion box="[926,1017,224,247]" country="Papua New Guinea" name="Western" pageId="21" pageNumber="282">Western</collectingRegion>
Indian Ocean: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Okamoto &amp; Gon" authorityYear="2018" box="[1189,1338,224,248]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="282" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bispinosus">
<emphasis box="[1189,1338,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="282">E. bispinosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Okamoto &amp; Gon" authorityYear="2018" box="[1353,1429,224,248]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="282" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="idai">
<emphasis box="[1353,1429,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="282">E. idai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Scott" authorityYear="1962" box="[151,274,260,284]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="282" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lenimen">
<emphasis box="[151,274,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="282">E. lenimen</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Parin &amp; Abramov" authorityYear="1986" box="[291,501,260,284]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="282" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="marimonticolus">
<emphasis box="[291,501,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="282">E. marimonticolus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Barnard" baseAuthorityYear="1927" box="[518,647,260,284]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="282" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="robustus">
<emphasis box="[518,647,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="282">E. robustus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Parin &amp; Abramov" authorityYear="1986" box="[716,887,260,284]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="282" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="waltersensis">
<emphasis box="[716,887,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="282">E. waltersensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mayer" authorityYear="1974" box="[905,1128,260,284]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="282" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pectinifer">
<emphasis box="[905,1128,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="282">Epigonus pectinifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from these species in having a slender tooth patch on the posterior half of tongue (rarely absent). In addition, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mayer" authorityYear="1974" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="282" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pectinifer">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="282">E. pectinifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs in having a sharp-pointed maxillary mustache-like processes (
<figureCitation box="[1104,1211,332,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="20.[151,250,1802,1824]" captionTargetBox="[188,1346,1182,1787]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[188,1398,1171,1787]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 16. Epigonus pectinifer. A: SAIAB 86380, 1 of 3 specimens, 152.6 mm SL; B: dorsal view of snout of SAIAB 193895, 1 of 4 specimens, 80.0 mm SL (arrows show the maxillary mustache-like processes)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1182201/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="282">Fig. 16B</figureCitation>
) (vs. absent in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Okamoto &amp; Gon" authorityYear="2018" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="282" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bispinosus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="282">E. bispinosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Okamoto &amp; Gon" authorityYear="2018" box="[283,357,368,392]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="282" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="idai">
<emphasis box="[283,357,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="282">E. idai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Parin &amp; Abramov" authorityYear="1986" box="[371,577,368,392]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="282" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="marimonticolus">
<emphasis box="[371,577,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="282">E. marimonticolus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Parin &amp; Abramov" authorityYear="1986" box="[637,807,368,392]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="282" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="waltersensis">
<emphasis box="[637,807,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="282">E. waltersensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and 10 + 15 vertebrae (vs. 11 + 
<quantity box="[1176,1233,367,392]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.556" pageId="21" pageNumber="282" unit="in" value="14.0">14 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Scott" authorityYear="1962" box="[1239,1358,368,392]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="282" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lenimen">
<emphasis box="[1239,1358,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="282">E. lenimen</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Barnard" baseAuthorityYear="1927" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="282" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="robustus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="282">E. robustus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). In a previous study of the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Giglioli" baseAuthorityYear="1880" box="[587,755,405,428]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="282" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="constanciae">
<emphasis box="[587,755,405,428]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="282">E. constanciae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group by Okamoto (2012: 251) erroneously described the dentition of the tongue of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mayer" authorityYear="1974" box="[442,581,440,464]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="282" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pectinifer">
<emphasis box="[442,581,440,464]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="282">E. pectinifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as “lingual teeth absent” in the key to the species of the group.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1436,151,536]" pageId="21" pageNumber="282">
We examined 14 specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mayer" authorityYear="1974" box="[550,689,476,500]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="282" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pectinifer">
<emphasis box="[550,689,476,500]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="282">E. pectinifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the Western South Indian Ocean deposited at SAIAB in this study. These specimens represent the first confirmed records of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mayer" authorityYear="1974" box="[866,1004,512,536]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="282" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pectinifer">
<emphasis box="[866,1004,512,536]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="282">E. pectinifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the Indian Ocean.
</paragraph>
